content.content:
Influenza, also known as the flu, is an infection caused by influenza viruses.

There are three main types – Type A, Type B and Type C. Influenza A(H1N1-2009), Influenza A(H3N2) and Influenza B are influenza viruses commonly circulating globally and in the community. Influenza C is associated with mild sporadic illness and occurs less frequently. Influenza can result in pneumonia, hospitalization or even death, especially in populations at higher risk of developing complications of influenza. Seasonal influenza vaccination is recommended to protect against influenza, especially to populations at higher risk of influenza complications. Medisave can be used for influenza vaccinations for persons at higher risk of developing influenza-related complications.

Source: Ministry of Health, Singapore (https://www.moh.gov.sg/diseases-updates/influenza )


Influenza Vaccination 

  • Participants of the talk may visit Raffles Medical for Flu (Quadrivalent) vaccination at $37.13.
  • Price of vaccination above include doctor’s consultation fee of $5.35.
  • Vaccination service is applicable at Raffles Medical clinics in Singapore, and not applicable at Raffles Executive Medical Centres, 24 Hour Emergency at Raffles Hospital, Raffles Health Screeners and Raffles Medical clinics at Transits 1, 2, 3 and 4.

Listed terms are subject to changes without prior notice. All prices are inclusive of GST.


Speaker: 

Dr. Salleh bin Omar BA Alkhatia
Deputy Medical Director, Raffles Medical

Dr Salleh is an experienced General Practitioner practising at Raffles Medical Terminal 3 clinic. He holds a Postgraduate Certificate in Civil Aviation Medicine from the Singapore Aviation Academy. In addition, he is a certified Designated Workplace Doctor.

SATS GROUP WELCOMES KEY MEMBERS OF WFS TO THE GLOBAL LEADERSHIP TEAM


Dear Colleagues,

I am pleased to inform you that we have expanded our global leadership team to include key members of WFS to harness the synergies and talent of our combined business.

With immediate effect, François Mirallié, Michael Simpson, and John Batten will join as members of the SATS Group Management Board (GMB) in their new upgraded roles. François will become Deputy Chief Executive Officer of WFS and take on an expanded role of overseeing WFS’ corporate functions. Further, Mike has been appointed Chief Executive Officer of Americas WFS, and John has been appointed Chief Executive Officer of Europe, Middle East, Africa, and Asia (EMEAA) WFS. They will work directly with me as we move ahead with our future strategy and plans as a Group. The roles and responsibilities of the WFS leadership team remain unchanged, but with the new direct reporting lines to me, Craig Smyth, the former CEO of WFS, is leaving the organisation. We thank Craig for his leadership and contributions during his time at WFS and wish him all the best in his future endeavours.

Incorporating members from WFS into this expanded team will enable the management team of SATS and WFS to adopt a holistic approach to growing our businesses and developing our talent. It will also deepen the cross-sharing of industry knowledge to promote best practices and develop a global mindset to strengthen our Singapore core.

Please join me in congratulating Francois, Michael and John on their new roles and welcoming them to the GMB.


Regards,

Kerry Mok

President & Chief Executive Officer
content.title: SATS Group welcomes key members of WFS to the Global Leadership Team
